---
<GuideLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/guides/aws-dynamodb-rcu-wcu-explained"
  lastUpdated="2026-01-20"
  faqs={[
    {
      q: "Why does item size matter for DynamoDB cost?",
      a: "Capacity consumption is sensitive to item size. Larger items consume more read/write capacity and increase storage cost.",
    },
    {
      q: "Do strongly consistent reads cost more?",
      a: "They can consume more read capacity than eventually consistent reads. For estimates, model both scenarios if you aren’t sure.",
    },
